2\tEarnings:              $17,567 x 23.4 days = $42,134\nDifference:    Straight forward caustic lifting down to Brazil. Initially late for her laycan due to mechanical issues on previous voyage, she was able to partially clean while awaiting port state clearance to sail at anchor.  Luckily, her previous voyages disport, and current voyages load port were both in Miss River, so ballast was minimal besides heading offshore to finish cleaning in deeper water.  As mentioned before we were able to clean in the river so 2.5 days of anticipated idle time for cleaning was saved.  Gasoil consumption increased by 32mt as a result of 3 additional days spent at the load port.  We did claim $29,880 under our bunker adjustment cls, rebilling $28k in shifting expense.  Important to also highlight an efficient laden passage decreased heavy fuel consumption by $50k \u2013 so ended up with $3k savings over all.  Additionally, port costs were $16k less than anticipated and $66k of demurrage was claimed.  \nImprovements:  None to note\n\n\nFIXTURE NOTE\n\nLady Amanda became open in New Orleans perfect for the 5th Alcoa lift and close to the end of the contract. Earnings are dreadfully low for what we estimated despite the negligible ballast due to changes in port cost structure. \n\nVessel\tLady Amanda Lift #5\nVoy#\t2202\nC/P Date\tNov 17th, 2021\nCharterer\tAlumar Consorcio do Alumina\nBroker\tKim Elbaek \u2013 NETCO\nStart\tNew Orleans\nLoad\tPlaquemine\nDischarge\tSao Luiz de Maranhao\nCargo\t38,300 mt CSS\nLay/Can\tSept 22 Aug \u2013 1 Sept\nRate\t$21,10pmt \u002B 85k River Differential\nComm\tBroker: 1.25%, Agent: 2%\nTCE\nPnL\t$15,600 for 21.0 days\nBreakeven bss 15,750/pd\nDemurrage\t$19,000"}],"offhireList":[{"id":192903,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":113584,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail